### API Testing Guide

### 1. Admin Login
POST http://localhost:3000/api/admin/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "SecurePassword123!"
}

### 2. Generate Admin Tokens (save JWT token from login response as @token)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/admin/generate-token
Authorization: Bearer @token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "quantity": 5,
  "purpose": "rating"
}

### 3. Request Phone Verification
POST http://localhost:3000/api/phone/request-verification
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "+37060123456",
  "ownerName": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "description": "I want to be verified as a trusted seller"
}

### 4. Get Pending Verifications (use @token from login)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/admin/pending-verifications
Authorization: Bearer @token

### 5. Approve Phone Verification
POST http://localhost:3000/api/admin/approve-verification
Authorization: Bearer @token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "requestId": "PASTE_REQUEST_ID_HERE",
  "generateTokens": false
}

### 6. Query Phone Number Reliability
GET http://localhost:3000/api/phone/query?phoneNumber=%2B37060123456

### 7. Add Rating (use token from generate-token response)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/rating/add
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "+37060123456",
  "ratedByPhoneNumber": "+37060999999",
  "reliabilityRating": 5,
  "timelinessRating": 4,
  "transactionAmount": 50,
  "comment": "Great transaction, very reliable",
  "token": "PASTE_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### 8. Health Check
GET http://localhost:3000/health
